&lt;/ul></description></item><item><title>AI tools for PKM and Obsidian</title><link>https://nicolevanderhoeven.github.io/blog/20230127-ai-tools-for-pkm-and-obsidian/</link><pubDate>Fri, 27 Jan 2023 16:39:00 +0100</pubDate><guid>https://nicolevanderhoeven.github.io/blog/20230127-ai-tools-for-pkm-and-obsidian/</guid><description>&lt;p>Here are some AI tools for learning and taking notes that I&amp;rsquo;ve incorporated into my processes. AI is a controversial topic, but it&amp;rsquo;s important to remember it&amp;rsquo;s just like any other technology: it&amp;rsquo;s only as good as the people that wield it. In this video, I show some ways I use artificial intelligence to improve my learning and note-taking rather than to replace them.&lt;/p>
